Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i think zack can always find something wrong with everything, the question is if is at an acceptable risk level. the biggest exposure that is see is that if notary nodes are evil, then they could mislead newly connecting nodes onto a false chain. however as long as users run make sure their node is in sync with the mainchain, then any false chain is meaningless, especially if bets are not made until after in sync.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the other issues is that if the source of data is hacked, then the data will be controllable. but my point is that these oracles are about what the online pricefeeds are returning, not their abstract price independent of a price source, so in a way if a price source is hacked, as long as the oracles are mining what the price source had, it is correct

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: from a practical point, having the chain not go off on forks due to data that is different on each node, this seems the most real issue. For over a week all 10 of the test nodes are in lock step. We havent pen tested it yet and likely there will be some issues found and fixed during that process, but as near as I can tell we are very close to having a trustless pricefeed that can be used to settle bets: http://159.69.45.70:8050/

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i think zack position is that anything that relies on elections is not secure as bribes can put attacker nodes as notaries. but this seems quite a theoretical thing and also the annual cycle makes it hard to bribe the elections to get your notaries in place so that they can cheat one time for the big bet that you will make later in the year

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so maybe some billionaire is secretly bribing all the KMD hodlers to elect his sleeper notary nodes so that when the world cup betting happens next, he can trick nodes that are not online into a betting frenzy before they make sure they are in sync with the real chain. This would of course mean that all the notary candidates must already be sleeper agents

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: OR... maybe that is just silly and not in any reality so we dont have to worry about the notarizations being for a fake chain. in any case that is a onetime attack as once it is found out, all the notaries that signed the fake chain are outed

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: In my opinion, the design is secure enough. zack would say that elections are involved so it cant be secure

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: but ask him, dont rely on my interpretation

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i think to be safe, just dont bet more than a million dollars at a time
